	<header class="page-header">
		<h1 class="page-title">About Dark Repos</h1>
		<p class="text-secondary">
			A comprehensive resource hub for retro game research, ROM hacking, and disassembly projects.
		</p>
	</header>

	<article class="about-content">
		<section class="mb-8">
			<h2>Our Mission</h2>
			<p>
				Dark Repos exists to preserve and document the technical details of classic video games.
				We believe that understanding how these games work at a fundamental level is essential
				for preservation, education, and the continued creativity of the ROM hacking community.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-8">
			<h2>What We Provide</h2>
			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
				<div class="card">
					<h3 class="text-md mb-2">ðŸ“š Game Documentation</h3>
					<p class="mb-0 text-secondary">
						Detailed technical documentation including ROM maps, RAM maps, data structures,
						and system descriptions for NES, SNES, GB, GBA, and Genesis games.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<h3 class="text-md mb-2">ðŸ”§ ROM Hacking Tools</h3>
					<p class="mb-0 text-secondary">
						Open-source tools for ROM analysis, graphics editing, text extraction,
						and disassembly work.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<h3 class="text-md mb-2">ðŸ“– Disassemblies</h3>
					<p class="mb-0 text-secondary">
						Annotated assembly source code with comprehensive labels, cross-references,
						and documentation.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<h3 class="text-md mb-2">ðŸ”— Wiki Resources</h3>
					<p class="mb-0 text-secondary">
						Community-editable wiki pages for collaborative documentation
						at <a href="https://games.darkrepos.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">games.darkrepos.com</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-8">
			<h2>Target Audience</h2>
			<ul class="about-list">
				<li><strong>ROM Hackers & Reverse Engineers</strong> - Technical details for creating game modifications</li>
				<li><strong>Retro Game Researchers</strong> - Academic and hobbyist documentation efforts</li>
				<li><strong>Game Preservation Enthusiasts</strong> - Ensuring classic games survive in technical detail</li>
				<li><strong>Speedrunners & Glitch Hunters</strong> - Understanding game mechanics at a deep level</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-8">
			<h2>Technology</h2>
			<p>
				This website is built with modern technologies while focusing on accessibility and performance:
			</p>
			<ul class="about-list">
				<li>.NET 10 Blazor with Interactive WebAssembly</li>
				<li>Custom CSS design system (no frameworks)</li>
				<li>SQLite database with FTS5 full-text search</li>
				<li>WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility compliance</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-8">
			<h2>Contributing</h2>
			<p>
				Dark Repos is an open-source project. We welcome contributions of all kinds:
			</p>
			<ul class="about-list">
				<li>Documentation improvements</li>
				<li>New game research and data</li>
				<li>Tool development</li>
				<li>Bug reports and feature requests</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Visit our <a href="https://github.com/TheAnsarya/GameInfo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub repository</a>
				to get started.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
